{"TopicId":137097,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Cooler loading screens.","CreatedByName":"Matuchkin","CreatedById":135127,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-16T16:38:38Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Matuchkin","CreatedById":135127,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-16T16:38:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot to be insuIting or demanding, but I do not quite like the recent loading screens. For one thing, smiling kerbals don\u0027t strike me as \u0022good looking\u0022 (though they do look very humorous, and reflect the game\u0027s style, which is very well thought-out). I put two example image-arrays for you to choose from, to see what style you support.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, what do you think, what should we do with the loading screens?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EImage array 1:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/79390-new-loading-screens-from-squad/\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;color:rgb(102,0,153);font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:0px;text-align:center;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(241,241,241);\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00229aa1cb65624921b7a690abc82e27e0ef.png\u0022 height=\u0022460\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.gyazo.com/9aa1cb65624921b7a690abc82e27e0ef.png\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;margin-top:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);background-position:0px 10px;\u0022 width=\u0022681\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/83570-105-b9-aerospace-release-600-updated-160216/\u0026amp;page=87\u0022 style=\u0022border:0px;color:rgb(102,0,153);font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:small;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:0px;text-align:cente